org.archive.cdxserver.processor

Interface BaseProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CDXListWriter, CDXToCaptureSearchResultsWriter, CDXToSearchResultWriter, CDXToUrlSearchResultWriter, CDXWriter, ClosestTimestampSorted, DupeCountProcessor, DupeTimestampBestStatusFilter, DupeTimestampLastBestStatusFilter, ForwardRevisitResolver, GroupCountProcessor, HttpCDXWriter, JsonWriter, LastNLineProcessor, MementoLinkWriter, PlainTextWriter, ReverseRevisitResolver, RevisitResolver, WrappedProcessor

    public interface BaseProcessor
    BaseProcessor is an interface for a receiver of CDXLines.

    Implementation may be final output formatter (CDXWriter subclasses for example), or an intermediary processor that performs transformation and/or filtering on the sequence of CDXLines.

    CDXServer starts from CDXWriter and builds up nested pipeline of BaseProcessors, and then calls following methods in sequence on the BaseProcessor at the top:

    1. modifyOutputFormat(FieldSplitFormat)
    2. begin()
    3. for each CDXLine:
      1. trackLine(CDXLine)
      2. writeLine(CDXLine)
    4. writeResumeKey(String) (if showResumeKey)
    5. end()

    • Method Detail

      • begin

        void begin()
        This method will be called just before looping over the sequence of CDX lines. Intermediary processor must call begin() on nested processor.

      • trackLine

        void trackLine(org.archive.format.cdx.CDXLine line)
        Called on each CDX line, just before timestamp range filtering (to and from parameters), regexp filtering, and collapser processing. Typically used for counting the number of CDX lines collapsed / grouped.
        Parameters:
        line - CDX line

      • writeLine

        int writeLine(org.archive.format.cdx.CDXLine line)
        Process line.
        Parameters:
        line - CDXLine
        Returns:
        1 if line is sent to output, 0 otherwise.

      • writeResumeKey

        void writeResumeKey(String resumeKey)
        Write resumption key. Only the final CDXWriter should do actual work. All intermediaries shall simply call writeResumeKey(resumeKey) on nested processor.
        Parameters:
        resumeKey -

      • end

        void end()
        Called at the end. Perform any clean ups / finalizations here. Intermediaries processor should call end() on nested processor.

      • modifyOutputFormat

        org.archive.format.cdx.FieldSplitFormat modifyOutputFormat(org.archive.format.cdx.FieldSplitFormat format)
        Return output format (list of fields), given input format format. Intermediaries should call modifyOutputFormat(format) on nested processor first, then make appropriate changes to it if they add/remove fields.
        Parameters:
        format - input format
        Returns:
        output format
